Mock Interview:

Q1. What is authentication, and why is it important in web applications?

Q2. Explain the difference between authentication and authorization.

Q3. What is bcrypt, and why is it used for password hashing in Node.js?

Q4. How do you integrate bcrypt into a Node.js application for securely storing user passwords?

Q5. Discuss the benefits of using salt when hashing passwords with bcrypt

Q6. Describe the process of implementing user authentication using JSON Web Tokens (JWT) in a Node.js application.

Q7. Explain why salting is important when hashing passwords with bcrypt.

Q8. Discuss the benefits of using JSON Web Tokens (JWT) for managing authenticated sessions in a stateless architecture.

Q9. Why is it essential to hash passwords using algorithms like bcrypt instead of storing them as plain text?

Q10. Explain how bcrypt manages the cost factor to adjust the computational intensity of password hashing.